        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
        <span class="policy-updated">Last updated — April 2026</span>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h3>What Spectre collects</h3>
          <p>
            <strong style="color:var(--green)">Nothing.</strong> Spectre Browser does not collect,
            transmit, or store any data about you or your browsing. All telemetry, crash reporting,
            and analytics are removed — there is no opt-out because there is nothing to opt out of.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h3>This website</h3>
          <p>
            The Spectre homepage does not use cookies, analytics, or tracking scripts.
            No third-party analytics provider has access to your visit. The only external
            request is to Google Fonts to load the Inter and JetBrains Mono typefaces.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h3>Extension store</h3>
          <p>
            Extensions are downloaded directly from Spectre's own servers. No request
            is made to Google's extension infrastructure. Each extension in the store
            is open source — you can audit exactly what you're installing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h3>GitHub</h3>
          <p>
            Spectre's source code is hosted on GitHub. Downloading a release means
            connecting to GitHub's servers, which are subject to
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
               target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy policy</a>.
            Spectre has no control over data GitHub collects during that request.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
          <h3>Updates</h3>
          <p>
            Spectre's auto-updater is disabled. You will never receive an automatic
            background update. New versions are announced on GitHub Releases, and
            you choose when and whether to upgrade.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-block">
